WebFrameWidgetImpl: survive a null WidgetInputHandlerManager on a
non-compositing widget.

The software-paint embedder path never creates the widget input handler
manager, and SetNeedsUnbufferedInputForDebugger dereferenced it
unconditionally. The inspector overlay calls it on every session detach
(InspectorOverlayAgent::disable -> ChromeClientImpl), so detaching a DevTools
session SIGSEGVd. Guard the null, mirroring the DidNavigate guard just below.

diff --git a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/web_frame_widget_impl.cc b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/web_frame_widget_impl.cc
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/web_frame_widget_impl.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/core/frame/web_frame_widget_impl.cc
@@ -4178,6 +4178,13 @@
 }
 
 void WebFrameWidgetImpl::SetNeedsUnbufferedInputForDebugger(bool unbuffered) {
+  // Null for a NON-COMPOSITING widget (a single-process embedder's
+  // software-paint view, which never creates the input handler manager). The
+  // inspector overlay calls this unconditionally on session detach
+  // (InspectorOverlayAgent::disable), which segfaulted. Same guard as
+  // DidNavigate below.
+  if (!widget_base_->widget_input_handler_manager())
+    return;
   widget_base_->widget_input_handler_manager()
       ->input_event_queue()
       ->SetNeedsUnbufferedInputForDebugger(unbuffered);
